[1] Czech Republic (Prague)
Date: Sat 28 Apr 2018
Source: Czech Radio [in French, machine trans., edited]
http://www.radio.cz/fr/rubrique/infos/70-cas-de-rougeole-a-prague-depuis-le-debut-de-lannee


As many as 70 cases of measles have been detected in Prague since the beginning of the year [2018]. The number of patients has increased by 9 in a week, according to the spokesman of the Health Station of the Czech capital Zbyněk Boublík. The Motol hospital in Prague, the largest hospital in the Czech capital, has decided to ban any new admission to the emergency room because of the contamination of an employee. Last week, there were 88 cases of measles in the country, and 59 in Prague. The Ministry of Health has to take stock of the situation in the country on Mon [30 Apr 2018].

A widespread phenomenon in Europe, which also affects the Czech Republic, measles is experiencing an unprecedented resurgence in recent years. Considered as a benign disease, the latter is transmitted mainly by air. The infected person becomes contagious the day before the appearance of the 1st symptoms, and for the following 5 days.

[Byline: Anna Kubišta]

